# The Ultimate Homeowner Hurricane Supply List (Roof & Exterior Edition)

Every Northeast Florida homeowner should keep a dedicated storm kit. Roof and exterior prep supplies can make the difference between minor cleanup and thousands in repairs. Hereâ€™s a supply list designed specifically for roof and exterior safety during hurricane season.

---

## 1. Roof & Repair Tools
- Heavy-duty tarp & roofing nails  
- Hammer, crowbar, duct tape  
- Ladder (stable footing)

ðŸ‘‰ *Save time and stress.* [Get the 6-page Storm Prep Checklist now.]({{ site.checklist_url }})

---

## 2. Safety Gear
- Work gloves, goggles, hard-soled boots  
- Flashlights, headlamps, extra batteries  
- Portable chargers for phones

---

## 3. Flood Protection
- Sandbags or flood barriers  
- Plastic sheeting to protect lower walls  
- Sump pump if in low-lying area

---

## 4. Survival Essentials
- Bottled water (1 gallon per person per day)  
- 3-day supply of non-perishable food  
- First aid kit and necessary medications

